:::::

The 2019 runners up came into the 2020 season looking for some redemption but ultimately fell flat. The Redwoods were right around the league average in total Fantasy Points, but were not quite a well rounded Fantasy team. Strong performances by the Redwoods Midfield, Defense and Goalie units made up for their less impressive Faceoff and Attack units. As a Club known for playing tough Defense with a star studded Midfield, the Redwoods did not disappoint in translating those strengths to Fantasy success. Games involving the Redwoods generally produced advantageous Fantasy situations in 2020 with their highest Fantasy Point total coming from their matchup with the Atlas where they scored a season high 11 goals. The Redwoods rolled in some areas and left Fantasy managers wanting more in others for the 2020 season. 

