:::


The Redwoods defense plays angry. Fantasy managers who targeted Redwoods' Defensemen in 2020 were certainly not angry. John Sexton at LSM and Garrett Epple at close defense led the Defense in Fantasy scoring with 55 and 54 Fantasy points respectively through caused turnovers and ground balls. Both Sexton and Epple made appearances on the "perfect lineup" for the first slate of games in the Championship Series. They proved their value as two top tier defenders and given where they were each drafted it was possible for Fantasy Managers to roster both players. The strategy of taking a top tier defenseman and LSM from the same team makes sense in theory as they occupy different areas of the field and do not necessarily compete for Fantasy Points. Sexton and Epple showed the blueprint for how this strategy can work and will be something to watch for in future seasons as well as similar situations in other Clubs.

